Reliability Requirements

5.1.  The system shall use HTTP/3 protocol that supports QUIC to accelerate reliable delivery of traffic. 
         5.1.1   The system shall have less than 1% rate of failure occurrence when 6500 concurrent users, during peak hours.
         
5.2.  The system shall have 0.01% chances of failure when a service request for downloading up to 250  Megabytes animation is sent.
        5.2.1.  The system shall have 0.05% failure rate when a service request for downloading 250 - 300 Megabytes animation is sent.
        
5.3.  The system shall have 99.9% uptime Availability with one hour downtime per year in worse scenarios.
     5.3.1. The system shall use AWS Load Balancing to prevent downtime and evenly distribute workload on servers.
     5.3.2. The system shall use AWS High Availability with S3 storage tier to reduce downtime.
     5.3.3. The system shall use AWS Elastic Disaster Recovery to prevent data loss.
     
5.4.  The system shall be compatible with AWS.
    5.4.1. The system shall use AWS Load Scaling services to store the word bank and animation component.
